The paper deals with auction mechanisms, which are a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of budget constraints and the comparison with the Market Clearing Price mechanism suggest a focus on algorithmic aspects (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.AI). The discussion of equilibrium deviations and efficiency properties also points to a connection with mechanism design (cs.EC) and learning theory (cs.LG).
